text: Willard is a small unincorporated community in Skamania County, in southwestern Washington. Willard is situated along the Little White Salmon River, 8 km (5 miles) north of the Columbia River and Washington State Route 14, at the southern boundary of the Gifford Pinchot National Forest. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Skamania County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Willard, Washington
